Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges, like steak fries. Core and quarter @Roma Tomato{2}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #foil-lined baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon} and a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. On other side of #baking sheet{}, toss tomatoes with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast until potatoes are crispy and tomatoes are very soft, ~{25-30%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Mix @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Dried Oregano{1%teaspoon}, @Paprika{1%teaspoon}, @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}, a drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper in a #small bowl{}.

Season @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} all over with salt and pepper. Rub with a drizzle of olive oil. Place on a second #baking sheet{}.

Add a layer of panko crust to top of each chicken breast, gently pressing to adhere. Pile topping as high as possible (you may have some left over).

Bake chicken until meat is cooked through and topping is golden brown, about ~{20%minutes}. Serve with potato wedges and roasted tomatoes.